{"about_the_game":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>Mango</strong> is a surrealist first-person adventure/puzzle game about art and derealization, featuring </p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> <strong>* trippy, psychedelic visuals</strong></p></li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> <strong>* intense psychological and philosophical undertones</strong></p></li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> <strong>* fragmented, lore-rich storytelling</strong> </p></li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> <strong>* experimental horror elements</strong></p></li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"> <strong>* and last but not least, an overarching feeling of NEVER knowing what to expect</strong>.</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">It explores the idea of a mind losing its grasp with reality, as reality  turns into a dream, and that dream turns into a nightmare. It has an off-kilter tone that  can shift from overly chill to downright scary. Often it resembles an acid trip, or an interactive fever dream.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">The game contains  ~8 hours of gameplay with lots of freaky action, even more freaky  fashion, deconstructed urban landscapes and/or dreamscapes, existential  angst, questionable parenting, a bit of driving, and a fair load of  straight-up madness. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">It has been described as simultaneously dadaist and hyper-realist in nature, both alien and also  deeply human,  as well as the story of a life, filtered through the eyes  of the mind.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Also, it has been described as WEIRD as hell ;)</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\">Get into It...</h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/1458690/extr